# SOLAT Naming & File Layout

When creating or renaming files, or when the user asks "what should I name X?", apply these rules. Output suggested names or a list of renames. No codegen; naming and layout only.

## Directories

- **kebab-case** (e.g. `property-profile`, `user-auth`)
- No spaces or underscores in directory names

## Engine (Python)

- **Modules:** `snake_case.py` (e.g. `broker_adapter.py`, `parquet_store.py`)
- **Test files:** `test_<module>.py` (e.g. `test_ig_client.py`)

## Desktop (TypeScript/React)

- **Components:** `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g. `StatusScreen.tsx`, `ExecutionPanel.tsx`)
- **Hooks:** `useCamelCase.ts` (e.g. `useEngineHealth.ts`, `useWebSocket.ts`)
- **Utilities:** `camelCase.ts`
- **Screens:** `PascalCase.tsx` under `apps/desktop/src/screens/` (e.g. `TerminalScreen.tsx`)

## Variables, types, constants

- **TypeScript/React:** `camelCase` for vars/props; `PascalCase` for types/interfaces; `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for constants
- **Python:** `snake_case` for functions/vars; `PascalCase` for classes; `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` for constants; single underscore for private

## Environment variables

- **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE** (e.g. `SOLAT_PORT`, `IG_API_KEY`, `MAX_RETRIES`)

## SOLAT layout (where new code goes)

- **Engine domain:** `engine/solat_engine/domain/` — Bar, Order, Signal, etc.
- **Engine API:** `engine/solat_engine/api/` — new routes → new or existing `*_routes.py`
- **Engine broker:** `engine/solat_engine/broker/ig/` — IG client, types, rate limit
- **Engine strategies:** `engine/solat_engine/strategies/` — elite8.py, indicators.py
- **Engine execution:** `engine/solat_engine/execution/` — router, risk, kill_switch
- **Engine data:** `engine/solat_engine/data/` — Parquet, aggregate, quality
- **Engine tests:** `engine/tests/` — `test_<module>.py`
- **Desktop components:** `apps/desktop/src/components/`
- **Desktop hooks:** `apps/desktop/src/hooks/`
- **Desktop screens:** `apps/desktop/src/screens/`

Avoid `any` in TypeScript. Use explicit types or interfaces.

